{"title_page": "2020 Jacksonville Jaguars season", "text_new": "{{short description|26th season in franchise history}}\n{{Infobox NFL season\n| team            = Jacksonville Jaguars\n| logo            = Jacksonville Jaguars wordmark.svg\n| year            = 2020\n| record          = \n| division_place  = \n| coach           = [[Doug Marrone]]\n| general manager = [[David Caldwell (American football executive)|David Caldwell]]\n| owner           = [[Shahid Khan]]\n| stadium         = [[TIAA Bank Field]]\n| playoffs        =\n| pro bowlers     =\n| uniform         = Jacksonville Jaguars uniforms 2018.png\n| shortnavlink    = Jaguars seasons\n}}\nThe [[2020 NFL season|2020 season]] will be the [[Jacksonville Jaguars]]' upcoming 26th season in the [[National Football League]] and their fourth under [[List of Jacksonville Jaguars head coaches|head coach]] [[Doug Marrone]]. They will attempt to improve on their [[2019 Jacksonville Jaguars season|6\u201310 record]] from the previous season and make the playoffs for the first time since [[2017 Jacksonville Jaguars season|2017]].\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n==Draft==\n{{main|2020 NFL Draft}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Jacksonville Jaguars|year=2020|border=2}}\"| 2020 Jacksonville Jaguars Draft\n|-\n! Round !! Selection !! Player !! Position !! College !! Notes\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"| [[List of Jacksonville Jaguars first-round draft picks|1]] || 9\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || <!--NOTE-->\n|-\n! 20\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || from [[2020 Los Angeles Rams season|Los Angeles Rams]]\n|-\n! 2 || 42\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || <!--NOTE-->\n|-\n! 3 || 73\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || <!--NOTE-->\n|-\n!rowspan=\"3\"| 4 || 116\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || <!--NOTE-->\n|-\n! 137\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || from [[2020 San Francisco 49ers season|San Francisco]] via [[2020 Denver Broncos season|Denver]]\n|-\n! 140\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || from [[2020 Chicago Bears season|Chicago]]\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"| 5 || 157\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || from [[2020 Baltimore Ravens season|Baltimore]] via [[2020 Atlanta Falcons season|Atlanta]]\n|-\n! 165\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || from Los Angeles Rams\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|  6 || 189\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || <!--NOTE-->\n|-\n! 206\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || from [[2020 Seattle Seahawks season|Seattle]]\n|-\n! 7 || 223\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || <!--NOTE-->\n|}\n'''Pre-draft trades'''\n*The [[Los Angeles Rams]] traded their [[2019 NFL Draft|2019]] third-round selection as well as their 2020 fifth-round selection to Jacksonville in exchange for defensive end [[Dante Fowler]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Rams acquire Jags DE Dante Fowler for draft picks|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/25128509/rams-acquire-jags-de-dante-fowler-draft-picks|website=ESPN.com|date=October 30, 2018|accessdate=October 30, 2018}}</ref>\n*The Seahawks traded their 2020 sixth-round selection to Jacksonville in exchange for Jacksonville's [[2019 NFL Draft|2019 sixth-round selection]].\n*The Jaguars traded their fifth-round selection to [[Pittsburgh Steelers|Pittsburgh]] in exchange for quarterback [[Joshua Dobbs]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jaguars.com/news/official-jaguars-trade-for-qb-dobbs|title=Official: Jaguars trade for QB Dobbs|publisher=Jacksonville Jaguars|date=September 9, 2019|accessdate=September 9, 2019}}</ref>\n*The Rams traded their first-round selection as well as their [[2021 NFL Draft|2021]] first and fourth-round selections to [[Jacksonville Jaguars|Jacksonville]] in exchange for cornerback [[Jalen Ramsey]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.jaguars.com/news/jaguars-trade-jalen-ramsey-to-the-los-angeles-rams|title=Ramsey traded to Los Angeles Rams|work=jaguars.com|date=October 15, 2019|access-date=October 17, 2019}}</ref>\n*The Jaguars traded cornerback [[A. J. Bouye]] to [[2020 Denver Broncos season|Denver]] in exchange for a fourth-round pick.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.denverbroncos.com/news/broncos-acquire-a-j-bouye-in-trade-with-jaguars|title= Broncos acquire A.J. Bouye in trade with Jaguars |work=DenverBroncos.com|date=March 18, 2020|access-date=March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n*The Jaguars traded quarterback [[Nick Foles]] to [[2020 Chicago Bears season|Chicago]] in exchange for a fourth-round pick.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2020/mar/18/nfl-free-agency-nick-foles-bears|title= Jaguars ship Nick Foles to Bears, one year after signing him to $88m deal |work=Theguardian.com|date=March 18, 2020|access-date=April 21, 2020}}</ref>\n*The Jaguars traded defensive end [[Calais Campbell]] to [[2020 Baltimore Ravens season|Baltimore]] in exchange for a fifth-round selection.<ref>{{cite web|title= Calais Campbell Is Officially a Raven, And Got a One-Year Extension |url=https://www.baltimoreravens.com/news/reports-ravens-acquire-calais-campbell-in-trade-with-jaguars|first=Clifton|last=Brown|website=BaltimoreRavens.com|date=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Staff==\n{{Jacksonville Jaguars staff}}\n\n==Current roster==\n{{Jacksonville Jaguars roster}}\n\n==Preseason==\nThe Jaguars' preseason opponents and schedule will be announced in the spring.\n\n==Regular season==\n<!--===Schedule===-->\n===2020 opponents===\nListed below are the Jaguars' opponents for [[2020 NFL season|2020]]. Exact dates and times will be announced in the spring.<ref>{{cite web |title=2020 Opponents Determined |url=https://nflcommunications.com/Pages/2020-Opponents-Determined.aspx |work=NFL Communications |date=December 30, 2019 |accessdate=December 30, 2019}}</ref> Two home games will be held at Wembley Stadium.<ref>{{cite web |last1=DiRocco |first1=Michael |titl