08 |location=Tokyo |language=Japanese |script-title=ja:\u30d5\u30a1\u30df\u901a\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u767d\u66f82008 |trans-title=Famitsu Game Whitebook 2008 |chapter=2007\u5e74\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u30bd\u30d5\u30c8\u5e74\u9593\u58f2\u4e0aTOP500 |trans-chapter=2007 Game Software Annual Sales Top 500 |chapter-url=http://geimin.net/da/db/2007_ne_fa/index.php |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150627100011/geimin.net/da/db/2007_ne_fa/index.php |archivedate=June 27, 2015 |accessdate=22 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}<ref name=\"ff7\">{{cite web|first=Andrew |last=Webster |url=https://arstechnica.com/gaming/news/2010/05/masterpiece-final-fantasy-vii.ars |title=Masterpiece: Final Fantasy VII |website=Ars Technica |date=May 2010 |accessdate=February 8, 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120130003235/http://arstechnica.com/gaming/news/2010/05/masterpiece-final-fantasy-vii.ars |archivedate=January 30, 2012 }}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|3\n|''[[Gran Turismo 2]]''\n|[[Polyphony Digital]]\n|[[Sony Computer Entertainment]]\n|{{dts|1999-12-11}}\n|9,370,000\n|align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"granturismo\"/>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|4\n|''[[Tekken 3]]''\n|[[Namco]]\n|[[Namco]]<br/>[[Sony Computer Entertainment]]\n|{{dts|1998-03-26}}\n|8,300,000\n|align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"tekken3\"/>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|5\n|''[[Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone (video game)|Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone]]''\n|[[Argonaut Games]]\n|[[Electronic Arts]]\n|{{dts|2001-11-15}}\n|8,000,000\n|align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"harrypotter\"/>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|6\n|''[[Tomb Raider (1996 video game)|Tomb Raider]]''\n|[[Core Design]]\n|[[Eidos Interactive]]\n|{{dts|1996-10-25}}\n|7,100,000\n|align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"tombraider\">{{cite news |url=http://kotaku.com/5224724/tomb-raider-lifetime-sales-show-off-lara-crofts-biggest-hits |title=Tomb Raider Lifetime Sales Show Off Lara Croft's Biggest Hits |last=McWhertor |first=Michael |work=[[Kotaku]] |publisher=[[Univision Communications]] |date=April 23, 2009 |accessdate=May 2, 2017 }}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|7\n|''[[Final Fantasy VIII]]''\n|[[Square (video game company)|Square]]\n|[[Square (video game company)|Square]]<br/>[[Sony Computer Entertainment]]\n|{{dts|1999-02-11}}\n|7,000,000\n|align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"wired\">{{cite web |url=https://www.wired.com/2001/05/deathmatch-2/ |title=Death Match: Your Guide to the Box Wars |last=Frauenfelder |first=Mark |work=[[Wired (magazine)|Wired]] |publisher=[[Cond\u00e9 Nast]] |date=May 1, 2005 |accessdate=May 2, 2017 }}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|8\n|''[[Crash Bandicoot (video game)|Crash Bandicoot]]''\n|[[Naughty Dog]]\n|[[Sony Computer Entertainment]]\n|{{dts|1996-09-09}}\n|6,820,000\n|align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"crash1\">{{cite book |title=Guinness World Records Gamer's Edition 2015 Ebook |date=November 6, 2014 |publisher=[[Guinness World Records]] |page=52 }}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|9\n|''[[Tomb Raider II]]''\n|[[Core Design]]\n|[[Eidos Interactive]]<br/>[[Victor Interactive]]\n|{{dts|1997-10-31}}\n|6,800,000\n|align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"tombraider\"/>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|10\n|''[[Metal Gear Solid (1998 video game)|Metal Gear Solid]]''\n|[[Konami]]\n|[[Konami]]\n|{{dts|1998-09-03}}\n|6,000,000\n|align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"metalgearsolid\">{{cite news |url=http://www.gameplanet.co.nz/features/i130089/Metal-Gear-Solid-3-Exclusive-For-Sony/ |title=Metal Gear Solid 3 Exclusive For Sony |last=Wright |first=Gary |publisher=[[Gameplanet]] |date=May 15, 2003 |accessdate=May 2, 2017 }}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|11\n|''[[Tomb Raider III]]''\n|[[Core Design]]\n|[[Eidos Interactive]]<br/>\n|{{dts|1998-11-20}}\n|5,900,000\n|align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"tombraider\"/>\n|-\n