1/http://www.elspa.com/?i=3944 |archive-date=May 6, 2010 |accessdate=Jan 30, 2020 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|109\n|''[[Colin McRae Rally (video game)|Colin McRae Rally]]''\n|[[Codemasters]]\n|[[Codemasters]]\n|{{dts|1998-07}}\n|1,000,000\n|align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2019-04-12-every-game-to-sell-over-1m-copies-in-the-uk |title=Here is every boxed game to sell over 1m copies in the UK |publisher=Gamesindustry.biz }}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|110\n|''[[NBA Live 2000]]''\n|[[EA Canada]]\n|[[Electronic Arts]]\n|{{dts|1999-10-31}}\n|1,000,000\n|align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"usplatinum\"/>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|111\n|''[[List of Simple series video games#Simple 1500 Series|Simple 1500 Series Vol. 1: The Mahjong]]''\n|Chat Noir<br/>[[Success (company)|Success]]\n|[[D3 Publisher]]\n|{{dts|1998}}\n|1,000,000\n|align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"jpplatinum\"/>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|112\n|''[[Street Fighter Alpha 3]]''\n|[[Capcom]]\n|[[Capcom]]\n|{{dts|1998-12-23}}\n|1,000,000\n|align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"capcom\"/>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|113\n|''[[Tekken (video game)|Tekken]]''\n|[[Namco]]\n|[[Namco]]<br/>[[Sony Computer Entertainment]]\n|{{dts|1995-03-31}}\n|1,000,000\n|align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"faq\">{{cite web|url=http://www.absolute-playstation.com/api_faqs/faq20.htm |title=PlayStation History \u2013 PlayStation Frequently Asked Questions |publisher=Absolute PlayStation |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110810075112/http://www.absolute-playstation.com/api_faqs/faq20.htm |archive-date=August 10, 2011 |accessdate=May 2, 2017 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|114\n|''[[WCW/nWo Thunder]]''\n|[[Inland Productions]]\n|[[THQ]]\n|{{dts|1998-12-31}}\n|1,000,000\n|align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"wcwnwo\">{{cite news |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/1999/05/15/breaking-news-wwf-meets-toukon-retsuden |title=Breaking News! WWF Meets Toukon Retsuden |work=[[IGN]] |publisher=[[Ziff Davis]] |date=May 15, 1999 |accessdate=May 2, 2017 }}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of best-selling video games]]\n*[[List of best-selling PlayStation 2 video games]]\n*[[List of best-selling PlayStation 3 video games]]\n*[[List of best-selling PlayStation 4 video games]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{vgbestsellers}}\n\n[[Category:PlayStation (console) games|PlayStation (console) games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation (brand)-related lists|Best-selling games]]\n[[Category:Lists of best-selling video games|PlayStation]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n[[File:PSX-Console-wController.jpg|thumb|250px|The original PlayStation model with the [[DualShock]] controller]]\nThe best-selling [[video game]] of all time on [[Sony Interactive Entertainment|Sony]]'s original [[PlayStation (console)|PlayStation]] console is ''[[Gran Turismo (1997 video game)|Gran Turismo]]''. A [[sim racing]] game developed by [[Polyphony Digital]], ''Gran Turismo'' was originally released in Japan on December 23, 1997, and went on to sell 10.85 million copies worldwide.<ref name=\"granturismo\">{{cite news |url=http://www.pcworld.com/article/145675/article.html |title=Gran Turismo Series Shipments Hit 50 Million |last=Williams |first=Martyn |work=[[PC World]] |publisher=[[International Data Group|IDG]] |date=May 9, 2008 |accessdate=May 2, 2017 }}</ref> The second-best-selling title on the console is ''[[Final Fantasy VII]]'' (1997), which sold over 10 million units.{{efn|name=FF7}}<ref name=\"ff7\"/> ''[[Gran Turismo 2]]'' (1999) sold 9.37 million units to become the third-best-selling PlayStation game of all time.<ref name=\"granturismo\"/> ''[[Tekken 3]]'' (1998) is the fourth-best-selling PlayStation game, with over 8.3 million units sold,<ref name=\"tekken3\">{{cite web |url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/how-tekken-7s-arcade-roots-are-shaping-its-console/1100-6447149/ |title=How Tekken 7's Arcade Roots Are Shaping Its Console Form |last=Tran |first=Edmond |work=[[GameSpot]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |date=January 23, 2017 |accessdate=May 2, 2017 }}</ref> while ''[[Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone (video game)|Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone]]'' is fifth.<ref name=\"harrypotter\">{{cite web |url=http://www.gameinformer.com/b/features/archive/2016/02/12/replay-harry-potter-and-the-sorcerer-39-s-stone.aspx?PageIndex=2 |title=Replay \u2013 Harry Potter And The Sorcerer's Stone |last=Hilliard |first=Kyle |work=[[Game Informer]] |publisher=[[GameStop]] |date=February 12, 2016 |accessdate=May 2, 2017 }}</ref>\n\nA total of 113 PlayStation games have sold one million units or more. Of those, 41 titles were published in one or more territory by [[Sony Computer Entertainment]] (SCEI). Other publishers with multiple million-selling games include [[Electronic Arts]] (13 games), [[Namco]] (10 games), [[Capcom]] (9 games), and [[Eidos Interactive]] (7 games). The developer with the most games to sell 1 million copies or more is [[Square (video game company)|Square]], with ten titles in the list of 113. The most popular franchise on PlayStation is ''[[Tomb Raider]]'' (25.9 million combined units), followed by ''[[Final Fantasy]]'' (24.15 million units), ''[[Crash Bandicoot]]'' (21.79 million units) and ''[[Gran Turismo (series)|Gran Turismo]]'' (20.22 million units). The oldest game on the list is [[Tekken (video game)|''Tekken'']], first released March 31, 1995 on the plaform, while the most recent is ''[[Dancing Stage Party Edition]]'', released November 15, 2002 when the [[PlayStation 2]] had been out for more than two years. \n\nAs of March 2007, a total of 962 million units of PlayStation software had been shipped worldwide.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scei.co.jp/corporate/data/bizdatapssoft_e.html |title=Cumulative Production Shipments of Software Titles |publisher=[[Sony Computer Entertainment]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080923062826/http://www.scei.co.jp/corporate/data/bizdatapssoft_e.html |archivedate=September 23, 2008 |accessdate=May 2, 2017 }}</ref>\n\n==Video games==\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|+Key\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"#FFFF99le=\"text-align:center;\"|\u2020\n|Game was [[Glossary of video game terms#pack-in game|shipped with PlayStation consoles]] during its lifetime\n|}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|+ List of best-selling PlayStation video games\n!scope=\"col\"|{{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!scope=\"col\"|Title\n!scope=\"col\"|Developer(s)\n!scope=\"col\"|Publisher(s)\n!scope=\"col\"|Release date\n!scope=\"col\"|Sales\n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"|Ref.\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|bgcolor=\"#FFFF99\"|''[[Gran Turismo (1997 video game)|Gran Turismo]]'' \u2020\n|[[Polyphony Digital]]\n|[[Sony Computer Entertainment]]\n|{{dts|1997-12-23}}\n|10,850,000\n|align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"granturismo\"/>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|2\n|''[[Final Fantasy VII]]''\n|[[Square (video game company)|Square]]\n|[[Square (video game company)|Square]]<br/>[[Sony Computer Entertainment]]\n|{{dts|1997-01-31}}\n|10,022,228\n|align=\"center\"|{{efn|name=FF7|''Final Fantasy VII'' (PlayStation)\n*{{As of|2005}} {{ndash}} 9.8{{nbsp}}million<ref>{{cite web|url=http://na.square-enix.com/e306/titles/ccff7/ |title=Crisis Core -Final Fantasy VII- |accessdate=December 15, 2019 |publisher=Square Enix|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080801053240/na.square-enix.com/e306/titles/ccff7/ | archivedate=August 1, 2008 | year=2006}}</ref>\n*''[[The Best (PlayStation range)|The Best]]'' (2006) {{ndash}} 158,458<ref>{{Cite book|title=Famits\u016b G\u0113mu Hakusho 2007 |publisher=[[Enterbrain]] |year=2007 |isbn=978-4-7577-3577-4 |location=Tokyo |page=387 |id={{JPNO|21240454}} |language=Japanes